<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/10404161-alex-shrugged"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1342665811i/10404161._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/10404161-alex-shrugged">Alex Shrugged</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Stephen Jay Gould passed away in 2002. He was Jewish (as am I). He was what is called in some circles a &quot;secular Jew&quot;. He did not practice the religio<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Stephen Jay Gould passed away in 2002. He was Jewish (as am I). He was what is called in some circles a "secular Jew". He did not practice the religion of Judaism in any formal sense. He called himself an agnostic. Given what I have read of him, that seems like a reasonable representation. His writing has been excellent... well above the norm... and his logic impeccable. I am very much impressed by him. <br /><br />From the science standpoint, he was a paleontologist, evolutionary biologist and historian. (I got that from Wikipedia, but he talks about being a paleontologist in this book.) He is suitably qualified to author this book.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
